title: Sudoku Solver
description: Write a program to solve a Sudoku puzzle by filling the empty cells. A sudoku solution must satisfy all of the following rules: Each of the digits 1-9 must occur exactly once in each row, each column, and each of the 9 3x3 sub-boxes of the grid. Empty cells are indicated by '.'. Input is a 9x9 grid where '.' represents empty cells. Output should be the completed 9x9 grid.
input_format: 9 lines, each containing 9 space-separated characters (1-9 or '.').

constraints.fixed: The input Sudoku puzzle will have a unique solution.
